{"word":"παρθένος","slug":"παρθένος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>παρϑένος, ου, ἡ</el>/<el>ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> unknown] ‘one who has had no sexual relationship’, <b>virgin<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of a female <b><a href='B:470 1:23'>Mt 1:23</a>; <a href='B:470 25:1'>25:1</a>, <a href='B:470 25:7'>7</a>, <a href='B:470 25:11'>11</a>; <a href='B:490 1:27'>Lk 1:27</a>; <a href='B:510 21:9'>Ac 21:9</a>; <a href='B:530 7:25'>1 Cor 7:25</a>, <a href='B:530 7:28'>28</a>, <a href='B:530 7:34'>34</a>, <a href='B:530 7:36-38'>36-38</a>; <a href='B:540 11:2'>2 Cor 11:2</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of a male <b><a href='B:730 14:4'>Rv 14:4</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:παρθενία\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Πάρθοι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}